      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOLD SIGHT (1) boasts strong form at this course and distance having won two times from four starts. Placed last time (29.68) at Sandown in a Grade 5 H, finishing third and beaten 4 lengths. Looks suited and should go close. PAW WINDER (6) was well supported last time but could only manage second (30.22), beaten 0.7 lengths. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Overdue and is among the main hopes. INDIAN PRINCE (2) is a classy type who was an all the way winner at this track (30.15) making it two straight wins. Form here is sound including two wins. Was a winner at his only start from this draw. In sparkling form and looks the one to beat again. MY MATE LEO (4) scored last time and appeals as a top-three prospect.",
